An worker came to fix the kitchen floor, I pretended to be just working from home, but actually I was editing "Dont Leave".
If only this damn file could be opened (OneDrive is really garbage).
*Hacker's voice* I'm in.
He started drilling, the sound is super loud. Great.
Turn the air purifier to the maximum level, it feels a bit too intense, but I really did smell the sawdust, so it's not entirely unreasonable to do so, and he's also against wearing a mask. And I do need to protect myself, don't I?
I really want to go back to sleep, but he left so I could sleep.
Good news is, the fourth chapter is finally edited!
The fifth chapter is very long, making people super anxious. Ye! It's really exciting.
Currently searching and replacing... ➡️ ellipsis, this chapter has 54 of them 😅
But I still want to hold on to this point. Most natural languages are incoherent, especially when people are emotionally excited.
The floor repair worker is cleaning with a vacuum cleaner, hoping that it means he is almost done.
He went out (sounds like) cutting something. I secretly looked at the progress. There is still a lot of work to do :(
There are 7 pages left in Chapter 5. It's still my favorite chapter, and the manuscript is in a relatively good state, mainly adjusting the layout, and making some small modifications to the active voice and conciseness. But I really need to rest, have a cup of tea, and that guy is still busy in my kitchen.
He started using the vacuum cleaner again. Hopefully, this is a good omen.
The worker who fixed the kitchen floor left!
He told me that he's going to fix the whole floor, but the landlord is too stingy and only wants to pay for the part of the floor that's already rotten in front of the door.
I'm having tea in the garden, and the air purifier in the kitchen is working hard to purify the air in the room!
